This program is is a Cloud storage system for simple files (size less than 100KB)
that was written in C using  the native Unix TCP/IP socket in- terface (i.e., socket calls)
Under the direction of the user (who will be given a list of commands) 
the user will be able to: Store a file in the cloud (copy file from client directory to server),
Retrieve a file from the cloud (reverse of previous process), copy a file locally (copy a file in client
directory), remove a file stored on the cloud (remove file stored on server), remove local file (remove
file stored in client directory). 

